In terms of product types, the demand for handheld RFID readers is on the rise due to their portability and ease of use, particularly favored for real-time asset and inventory tracking needs. Fixed RFID readers are gaining traction in industries like manufacturing and logistics where continuous monitoring throughout the supply chain is crucial for operational efficiency. The frequency segmentation allows businesses to choose RFID systems that align with their specific requirements, whether for short-range applications like access control or long-range applications like supply chain management. This diverse range of options enhances the adaptability of RFID technology across different sectors.

